      "content": "The established neighborhood likely offers more predictable, stable returns, as long-term residents tend to maintain property values well. However, the rapid turnover in the high-density area might present a quicker path to profit if you can capitalize on the influx of new, often transient, populations. The risk in the older area is stagnation, while the risk in the newer area is instability and unpredictable demand.",
